[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating test setup**\n\nI'm wondering if the \"beyond normal generated test scaffold\" is necessary for meaningful coverage. The current build uses jvmArgs for DNS internals, but regular tests may not need DNS. The compilation errors seem to stem from removed TypedActor classes rather than setup issues. I think the workflow should be adjusted to prevent issues with removed classes. The agent_guidance could help steer clear of unnecessary API usage. I also need to consider whether additional Maven dependencies are required, but substantial coverage should be possible with just pekko-actor.\n\n**Considering scaffold requirements**\n\nI’m questioning whether that’s what's meant by \"beyond normal scaffold.\" It’s not deterministic, which makes me think it could be more about advisory preparation with just agent guidance instead. That might simplify things, allowing for a clearer approach to mitigate uncertainty. I wonder how to best balance these elements to ensure everything runs smoothly. I really want to make sure that the user gets the best outcome possible from this setup!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_04cb24e33ed13aaf016a42b28ac5e48190aa8b498c80faed47\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQrKVCCW1nO6PtqKq5AKxmod2doeS_Kb8uhwZ_qPhYN_vMcjtp_HB01D3X5zwZkYjMfn7C6-fQVh2SakDs91j98gQycD3OgTFdbnlLHx5hF5sOHg1nhBKbrnCiliAYtizN-o614fW6dtTdNHECAnVANjZj7rE7UJucWE6qQqKKwEen0Sd0IPmIfL7KrqRppMXUYWspvXFt2hSF4pkx9i1lQSFtu1cEcpFCoGnWveeu11SkznzMxokfywwvR7saxCeFHfpGwPP5RDOer1OCl5Go5ZXq70IFvIL4zAwI9H2iBk92V-sSnFtp-RgNFWkTMpkkmCd7ceUbG25yK0FW9o1zesBhi6tSVPraXMDww6ypSrWkd5j9pgLCbO45cRq_OAhgZeo3R5or5GKwXpY-F9c8vMRLwxld32Dov5xMLbo-UgzLfxTbW1y7AF3ZTGnTuwToK2sZ5uQKeQkvUDMPdIZsClhmlgNz1xFmBkzAJ5S-GsOZmxVdn0zn_losRj20UZbluZC_gM9Al8k7SeOTJapgp9SYlGQ_HKYgaHhr4ElsTWUUyMpFMAP_ljUYoV6G6Yi9K1XYUWhGD5T4xxkUQeaEyd0OezJ30TJ4AN0Cz0eKA-79hwLwULrXCNsnnu2